      • basePrototype

        default BaseObject basePrototype()
        Description copied from interface: BaseObject
        The value of the [[Prototype]] property must be either an object or null, and every [[Prototype]] chain must have finite length (that is, starting from any object, recursively accessing the [[Prototype]] property must eventually lead to a null value). Whether or not a native object can have a host object as its [[Prototype]] depends on the implementation.

      • toBinary

        default BinaryReplyAnswer<?> toBinary()
                               throws Flow.FlowOperationException
        Returns a response whose isEmpty(), isBinary() or isFile() method will return true and getBinary() or getFile() will return a binary non-null representation of a response. When a response is already meets conditions secified this method should return exactly the SAME response object. The "Character-Encoding" of "Content-Type" attributes of a current response and "Accept-Charset" or "Accept-Type" attributes of current query should be considered when possible. "UTF-8" encoding should be used by default.
        Specified by:
        toBinary in interface BaseMessage
        Specified by:
        toBinary in interface BodyAccessUnknown
        Returns:
        reply
        Throws:
        Flow.FlowOperationException

      • toCharacter

        default CharacterReplyAnswer<?> toCharacter()
                                     throws Flow.FlowOperationException
        Returns a response whose isEmpty(), isCharacter() or isObject() method will return true and getText() or getObject() will return a non-null stringual representation of a response. When a response is already meets conditions secified this method should return exactly the SAME response object. The "Character-Encoding" attribute of a current response and "Accept-Charset" attribute of current query should be considered when possible. "UTF-8" encoding should be used by default.
        Specified by:
